    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.13.25"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">25</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">STATE NORMAL SCHOOL AND TEACHERS COLLEGE
                        <lb/>
                    U.S. CONN, PRESIDENT
                        <lb/>
                    WAYNE, NEBRASKA
                        <lb/>
                
                    SECRETARY TO THE PRESIDENT
                        <lb/>
                    ELVA B. BROCKWAY</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>October 11, 1928</dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>St. Louis, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I observe by the daily paper that you are to receive the honorary title of Doctor of Laws from Creighton University on the 19th of this month. Will it not be possible for you to come to Wayne either before or immediately following this date? If you could come up on Thursday we would like to have you give a number of talks to groups of students in English, or if you can come and remain until Monday we could use you in the same capacity.</p>
                
                <p>If you cannot be with us during a school day come anyway and make us a visit and be the guest of myself, Mrs. Conn and our daughter who is now at home. We are building a girls dormitory and have christened it Neihardt Hall. We had in mind to have you with us at the formal opening of it about the first of January but a visit now will be entirely in order and much appreciated by all of us as you have not been here for some time.</p>
                
                <p>We will be looking for you and I would like to have you drop me a line saying you can come.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Very truly,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>US Conn</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <note type="recipient">Dr. Conn</note>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
